  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  ages 14-19 years&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  attending high school (peak period for insufficient and delayed sleep)&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  completion of bariatric surgery procedure (i.e., vertical sleeve gastrectomy) within&#xD;
             the past 2 years but not less than 6 months prior to study participation&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  All must also be Tanner Stage 5&#xD;
&#xD;
        Exclusion Criteria:&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  regular use of medications affecting sleep (e.g., stimulants, atypical antipsychotics,&#xD;
             melatonin or other sleep aids) or insulin resistance (systemic steroids, other oral&#xD;
             diabetes medications)&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  HbA1c â‰¥6.5%&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  intelligence quotient (IQ) &lt;70 or severe mental illness&#xD;
